This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the training and generalization of over-parametrized neural networks. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it focuses on the behavior of neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as neural networks are a popular tool in AI research. The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY), which are other possible sub-categories.
